{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"41c4ce93-aee7-4956-9c7f-c4126f9f704e","content":"Here's what you need for NativeAOT crash dump collection:\n\n**Key points:**\n- NativeAOT doesn't bundle `createdump`, so you must set `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` explicitly.\n- Dumps go to a volume so they survive pod restarts.\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: my-app\n    env:\n    # Enable automatic mini dump on crash\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n      value: \"1\"\n    # Dump type: 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n      value: \"4\"\n    # Path to createdump (required for NativeAOT)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n      value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n    # Dump file name pattern (%d = PID, %t = timestamp)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n      value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%d.%t\"\n    volumeMounts:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- **`DbgMiniDumpType=4`** (Full) gives the most debugging info; use `2` (Heap) to save space.\n- **`emptyDir`** is ephemeral — switch to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod deletion.\n- Ensure `/opt/tools/createdump` has execute permissions (`chmod +x`).\n- The `%d` and `%t` tokens prevent overwrites on repeated crashes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9eebcfa-0f0e-4c88-b701-39536707e63c","outputTokens":455,"requestId":"D801:11B452:104F0FE:12A3709:69F2B552"},"id":"5ba1f3ea-1cfc-42be-8c3f-27f0e5f06c86","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:50:21.361Z","parentId":"3b692756-fdc5-4381-91b4-9fb3a649f806"}
